How long did you wait?

With the default retryDelay (900 seconds) and maxRetries (30), a single 
URI (either a dns:baddddd-hostname.com or then 
http://baddddd-hostname.com/) will take 7.5 hours to exhaust all its 
retries, and thus show up as a final failure in crawl.log.

You can set these lower, but only at the risk that transient 
network/server issues cause the crawler to give up on URIs that would be 
available with just a little more patience. (And, the maxRetries should 
always be 3 or more, to accommodate some usual crawler-code practices 
that sometimes notice a URI should be deferred until after a 
prerequisite is fetched, so trigger using up retries even when there are 
no network/server problems.)

- Gordon

